# Form Development Guidelines

## Multi-Step Form Architecture
This project uses a step-based form system. Follow the pattern established in [src/components/form/steps/](mdc:src/components/form/steps/).

### Step Component Structure
Each step should follow this pattern (see [src/components/form/steps/Step1.js](mdc:src/components/form/steps/Step1.js)):

```jsx
import { useSelector, useDispatch } from 'react-redux';
import { updateFormData } from '@/store/slices/formSlice';

const StepN = () => {
  const dispatch = useDispatch();
  const formData = useSelector(state => state.form);
  
  const handleChange = (field, value) => {
    dispatch(updateFormData({ [field]: value }));
  };
  
  return (
    // Step content
  );
};
```

### Form Controls
- Use standardized controls from [src/components/form/controls/](mdc:src/components/form/controls/)
- InputRow component: [src/components/form/controls/InputRow.jsx](mdc:src/components/form/controls/InputRow.jsx)
- Select component: [src/components/form/controls/InputRowSelect.jsx](mdc:src/components/form/controls/InputRowSelect.jsx)

### State Management
- All form data goes through Redux store: [src/store/slices/formSlice.js](mdc:src/store/slices/formSlice.js)
- Use `updateFormData` action for field updates
- Access form state with `useSelector(state => state.form)`

### Navigation
- Form navigation logic in [src/components/form/FormNav.js](mdc:src/components/form/FormNav.js)
- Handle step validation before allowing navigation
- Use consistent navigation patterns across all steps

### Styling
- Follow SCSS patterns from [src/scss/components/_form.scss](mdc:src/scss/components/_form.scss)
- Use form-specific CSS classes for consistent styling
- Maintain responsive design principles

## Item Counters & Interactive Elements
- Use ItemCounter component from [src/components/form/steps/ItemCounter.js](mdc:src/components/form/steps/ItemCounter.js)
- Follow established patterns for plus/minus controls
- Implement proper validation for numeric inputs
